            <title>[GROOVY-6778] groovy scripts file path name containing &quot;e-n&quot; raises &quot;java.io.IOException: Invalid argument&quot;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-6778</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Reproducing steps:&lt;br/&gt;
1. Create a groovy script named &quot;e-n.groovy&quot; (contents doesn&apos;t matter)&lt;br/&gt;
2. Run &quot;groovy.bat e-n.groovy&quot;, bang!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;Caught: java.io.IOException: Invalid argument
java.io.IOException: Invalid argument
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
                <environment>Windows Server 2012 / Windows 8.1&lt;br/&gt;
JDK 7 / 8&lt;br/&gt;
Groovy 2.2.1 / 2.3.0</environment>
